[playful music]

269
00:12:37,458 --> 00:12:38,791
[giggles]

270
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:39,833
What?

271
00:12:40,041 --> 00:12:41,083
Kaiser?

272
00:12:42,083 --> 00:12:44,041
Now, lick him
from head to toe.

273
00:12:47,083 --> 00:12:48,083
No!

274
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:49,125
Hey, what are you doing?

275
00:12:49,333 --> 00:12:50,125
Stop it, Kaiser!

276
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:51,166
Why are you licking me?

277
00:12:51,375 --> 00:12:52,166
[sloppy licking]

278
00:12:52,375 --> 00:12:53,666
[yelps]

279
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:56,500
Kaiser, heel.

280
00:12:56,708 --> 00:12:57,708
Leave me alone!

281
00:12:57,916 --> 00:13:00,333
Oh, it's so sticky.

282
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,666
[giggles]

283
00:13:03,875 --> 00:13:04,958
Golly.

284
00:13:05,708 --> 00:13:06,666
Thanks a lot.

285
00:13:06,875 --> 00:13:08,500
You really saved us.

286
00:13:10,333 --> 00:13:11,916
That's the dark
power dwelling

287
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:15,125
within Rirui, unleashed
in the name of justice.

288
00:13:15,333 --> 00:13:16,333
So cool!

289
00:13:16,541 --> 00:13:18,125
What are you going on about?

290
00:13:19,125 --> 00:13:20,250
That's awesome!

291
00:13:20,458 --> 00:13:21,291
Yeah, it is.

292
00:13:21,291 --> 00:13:23,500
I wish I had a dark power.

293
00:13:23,708 --> 00:13:25,166
[GIRL]
You said your name's Rirui?

294
00:13:25,375 --> 00:13:26,666
You wanna hang out with us,

295
00:13:26,666 --> 00:13:29,125
and we can all
make deer god masks together?

296
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:30,583
[RIRUI]
Sure, let's do it!

297
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:34,458
Really? You wound up
making masks with them?

298
00:13:34,666 --> 00:13:37,500
Yeah! We promised to meet up
and play with each other

299
00:13:37,708 --> 00:13:39,541
on the day of the festival.

300
00:13:39,750 --> 00:13:41,583
And, oh, yeah,
me and Anya are going

301
00:13:41,791 --> 00:13:43,541
to run a meat stall together.

302
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:45,083
[HAJIME]
Like a vendor stall?

303
00:13:45,291 --> 00:13:46,375
We're going
to cook up the meat

304
00:13:46,583 --> 00:13:48,333
from our hunts in the dungeon.

305
00:13:49,458 --> 00:13:50,708
[giggle]

306
00:13:50,916 --> 00:13:53,666
I'm super excited
about the festival.

307
00:13:53,875 --> 00:13:57,125
[gentle music]

308
00:13:57,333 --> 00:13:59,791
[snore]

309
00:14:02,458 --> 00:14:06,333
That's right, Rirui's stall
is doing big business.

310
00:14:06,541 --> 00:14:07,291
[chuckles]

311
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:10,666
♪ ♪

312
00:14:10,875 --> 00:14:12,583
Her first festival.

313
00:14:14,416 --> 00:14:15,875
Not really the best memories

314
00:14:16,083 --> 00:14:17,583
from when I was a kid.

315
00:14:18,833 --> 00:14:22,416
Just staring at the commotion
from the alleys.

316
00:14:22,625 --> 00:14:25,125
All I could ever do was watch.

317
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:29,708
All that fun stuff
I missed out on.

318
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:36,208
I'm glad Rirui will
actually get to enjoy it.

319
00:14:36,416 --> 00:14:43,458
♪ ♪

320
00:14:48,166 --> 00:14:50,291
I'm sensing magic beasts.

321
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:53,458
[breathing heavily]

322
00:14:55,458 --> 00:14:56,416
[roar]

323
00:14:56,625 --> 00:14:57,458
[WATCHMAN 1]
Here they come!

324
00:14:57,458 --> 00:14:58,500
[WATCHMAN 2]
Pull over!

325
00:14:58,500 --> 00:14:59,500
[WATCHMAN 3]
Get ready for them.

326
00:14:59,708 --> 00:15:02,625
[growling]

327
00:15:03,666 --> 00:15:05,041
[BOTH scream]

328
00:15:06,583 --> 00:15:08,875
[dramatic music, grunting]

329
00:15:09,083 --> 00:15:14,333
♪ ♪

330
00:15:14,541 --> 00:15:16,375
Damn, what's with
these rabbit bears

331
00:15:16,583 --> 00:15:17,958
attacking all of a sudden?

332
00:15:18,875 --> 00:15:20,791
Oh, no, it got past me.

333
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:24,250
[footsteps thudding]

334
00:15:24,458 --> 00:15:31,166
♪ ♪

335
00:15:31,375 --> 00:15:33,791
Oh, adventurer.

336
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:40,000
♪ ♪

337
00:15:40,208 --> 00:15:41,458
What's up?

338
00:15:41,458 --> 00:15:44,291
Um, well, a massive
horde of them suddenly

339
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:46,833
started jumping over the gate.

340
00:15:47,041 --> 00:15:48,750
I've never seen
anything like it.

341
00:15:48,958 --> 00:15:49,750
Weird.

342
00:15:49,958 --> 00:15:51,125
What's causing it?

343
00:15:52,375 --> 00:15:55,250
Wait, there are
mountain wolves too?

344
00:15:58,333 --> 00:16:01,750
Don't you think the moon
is just lovely tonight?

345
00:16:01,958 --> 00:16:02,750
Chair?

346
00:16:02,958 --> 00:16:04,041
Yes, ma'am.

347
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:09,291
You landed
your marks perfectly.

348
00:16:09,500 --> 00:16:10,666
Who's a good boy?

349
00:16:10,875 --> 00:16:13,333
Me? Oh, thank you
so much, mistress.

350
00:16:13,541 --> 00:16:15,708
I didn't ask
for a talking magic chair.

351
00:16:15,916 --> 00:16:17,000
[slap thuds]

352
00:16:17,208 --> 00:16:18,750
[shudders]

353
00:16:18,958 --> 00:16:20,333
[VERONICA] You want
your reward, swine?

354
00:16:20,541 --> 00:16:22,000
-[VERONICA] Here it is.
-[MAN] Oh, thank you.

355
00:16:22,208 --> 00:16:23,041
Oh, thank you.

356
00:16:23,250 --> 00:16:24,541
[WOMAN] Here's a bonus.

357
00:16:24,541 --> 00:16:26,875
You've got plenty
of energy, given the hour.

358
00:16:27,083 --> 00:16:29,541
Well, the full
moon is soon upon us.

359
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:31,458
You know us, ancient species.

360
00:16:31,666 --> 00:16:33,750
It stirs our blood.

361
00:16:33,958 --> 00:16:35,208
Huh?

362
00:16:35,416 --> 00:16:38,000
It doesn't even look
three-quarters full.

363
00:16:38,208 --> 00:16:41,375
You-- jeez, you are hopeless.

364
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:44,833
I clearly explained this all
to you when you adopted Rirui.

365
00:16:45,041 --> 00:16:47,083
If you intend to raise
one of my kind,

366
00:16:47,291 --> 00:16:48,333
you better get it together.

367
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:49,333
All right, I got it.

368
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:51,583
It's under control.

369
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:53,500
Have a good night.

370
00:16:54,291 --> 00:16:55,541
[shudders]

371
00:16:56,291 --> 00:16:58,458
[grunts]

372
00:17:01,250 --> 00:17:03,791
So their blood starts
to stir as the full moon

373
00:17:04,000 --> 00:17:05,416
approaches, huh?

374
00:17:09,708 --> 00:17:11,958
[owl hoots]

375
00:17:16,125 --> 00:17:19,333
[breathing heavily]

376
00:17:27,958 --> 00:17:32,750
Strange, her charm
marking, it was glowing.

377
00:17:35,041 --> 00:17:36,416
Welcome to our stall.

378
00:17:36,625 --> 00:17:41,125
What can I get you?
[giggles] Anya, you've got

379
00:17:41,333 --> 00:17:42,708
to put more meat on the grill.

380
00:17:42,916 --> 00:17:45,208
This line's getting huge.

381
00:17:48,291 --> 00:17:51,000
This is going
to be so amazing.

382
00:17:51,208 --> 00:17:54,166
We're going to need to gather
up a whole bunch of meat.

383
00:17:54,375 --> 00:17:56,291
Rirui's going
to hunt her heart out.

384
00:17:56,500 --> 00:17:58,166
Rirui, Anyango.

385
00:17:58,375 --> 00:17:59,875
-Huh?
-Huh?

386
00:17:59,875 --> 00:18:03,166
Someone said you girls are
going to be running a stall.

387
00:18:04,166 --> 00:18:06,250
Yep, we'll be
grilling up some meat.

388
00:18:06,458 --> 00:18:08,333
Count on me as a customer.

389
00:18:08,541 --> 00:18:09,375
Yay!

390
00:18:09,583 --> 00:18:11,125
We'll be ready.

391
00:18:11,333 --> 00:18:13,958
Two kids running
a stall, could be tough.

392
00:18:14,166 --> 00:18:16,083
If it turns out you
girls need any help,

393
00:18:16,291 --> 00:18:17,583
just give us a shout.

394
00:18:17,791 --> 00:18:18,708
Oh, thank you.

395
00:18:18,916 --> 00:18:20,750
That's so nice.

396
00:18:20,958 --> 00:18:22,958
We better get going.

397
00:18:23,166 --> 00:18:25,166
[giggling]

398
00:18:25,375 --> 00:18:26,583
[RIRUI] I can't wait
to start cooking.

399
00:18:26,791 --> 00:18:27,708
Rirui.

400
00:18:27,916 --> 00:18:29,041
-Huh?
-Huh?

401
00:18:29,041 --> 00:18:30,958
You have any weird
dreams last night,

402
00:18:31,166 --> 00:18:32,958
maybe like a violent one?

403
00:18:33,166 --> 00:18:35,750
Uh, I don't think so.

404
00:18:37,625 --> 00:18:39,500
Did you dream
about your powers?

405
00:18:39,708 --> 00:18:40,833
Were you using them?

406
00:18:41,041 --> 00:18:42,500
How could I do that?

407
00:18:42,708 --> 00:18:44,916
I was sound asleep
all night long.

408
00:18:45,125 --> 00:18:45,916
Why?

409
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:47,208
Is something wrong?

410
00:18:48,541 --> 00:18:49,791
Sorry.

411
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,083
It's nothing.

412
00:18:52,875 --> 00:18:54,541
It went that way!

413
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:56,541
[footsteps thudding]

414
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:58,041
[yells]

415
00:18:58,250 --> 00:19:01,958
[thuds]

416
00:19:02,166 --> 00:19:04,708
[panting]

417
00:19:09,916 --> 00:19:12,333
One skewer, coming
right up, sir.

418
00:19:12,541 --> 00:19:14,583
[giggles]

419
00:19:21,041 --> 00:19:23,166
[OLIVE] Is
everything all right?

420
00:19:23,375 --> 00:19:25,500
You rarely look so concerned.

421
00:19:25,708 --> 00:19:27,125
What's bothering you?

422
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:29,250
Mm.

423
00:19:29,458 --> 00:19:32,500
Well, I'm guessing
you've heard all about

424
00:19:32,708 --> 00:19:35,166
this magic
beast situation, right?

425
00:19:35,375 --> 00:19:36,750
The nightly attacks, I mean.

426
00:19:36,958 --> 00:19:38,500
[OLIVE]
I should have known.

427
00:19:38,708 --> 00:19:40,791
Thank you for pitching
in every night.

428
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:42,083
We've all been so worried,

429
00:19:42,291 --> 00:19:45,000
and nobody knows
what's causing it.

430
00:19:45,208 --> 00:19:48,166
Once we do,
I'm putting an end to it.

431
00:19:48,375 --> 00:19:49,625
Let's bring Cocko in.

432
00:19:49,833 --> 00:19:51,875
I think it's time
for a strategy meeting.

433
00:19:52,083 --> 00:19:53,666
Yeah, let's get real.

434
00:19:55,041 --> 00:19:56,708
I should have known.

435
00:19:56,916 --> 00:19:59,125
Of course, the village
would be troubled by this.

436
00:20:01,041 --> 00:20:03,875
So, something on your mind?

437
00:20:06,416 --> 00:20:08,791
No, nothing at all.

438
00:20:10,166 --> 00:20:11,583
[thuds]

439
00:20:12,958 --> 00:20:15,333
[gentle music]

440
00:20:15,541 --> 00:20:22,583
♪ ♪

441
00:20:23,375 --> 00:20:25,458
[HAJIME]
Rirui, wake up.

442
00:20:26,250 --> 00:20:27,500
Huh?

443
00:20:33,625 --> 00:20:36,166
Whoa, why the heck
would my arm be glowing?

444
00:20:37,333 --> 00:20:38,958
Can you control it?

445
00:20:39,166 --> 00:20:40,416
Try to stop it.

446
00:20:40,625 --> 00:20:43,208
[straining]

447
00:20:45,708 --> 00:20:48,625
No, it doesn't seem like I can.

448
00:20:48,833 --> 00:20:50,166
It's OK.

449
00:20:50,375 --> 00:20:51,500
But what's happening?

450
00:20:51,708 --> 00:20:53,291
Why is my arm all glowy?

451
00:20:53,791 --> 00:20:55,791
Hmm. My guess?

452
00:20:57,708 --> 00:20:59,375
It's a power
sealed within you.

453
00:20:59,583 --> 00:21:00,791
[gasp]

454
00:21:00,791 --> 00:21:02,416
And this means
your dark forbidden power

455
00:21:02,625 --> 00:21:05,958
is beginning to stir and fight
its way up to the surface.

456
00:21:06,333 --> 00:21:07,833
Seriously?

457
00:21:08,041 --> 00:21:11,000
Well, Rirui can't believe it.

458
00:21:11,208 --> 00:21:12,541
Can it really be true?

459
00:21:12,750 --> 00:21:15,041
Is my dark dragon
trying to awaken?

460
00:21:15,250 --> 00:21:17,541
Man, you really
love dragons, huh?

461
00:21:19,250 --> 00:21:22,041
[RIRUI] Well, it's obvious
what I have to do now.

462
00:21:22,250 --> 00:21:23,125
Huh?

463
00:21:23,333 --> 00:21:24,625
Yes, Rirui will tame

464
00:21:24,833 --> 00:21:27,041
and fiercely
wield this dark power.

465
00:21:27,250 --> 00:21:29,458
And then I'll use it
to help every last person

466
00:21:29,666 --> 00:21:30,833
in the village.

467
00:21:31,041 --> 00:21:32,291
Well...

468
00:21:34,083 --> 00:21:37,291
that's nice,
but keep that power a secret.

469
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:38,791
Huh?

470
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,833
But why can't I share it?

471
00:21:41,041 --> 00:21:42,500
Hm, uh...

472
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:46,166
Well, it sounds cool, right?

473
00:21:46,375 --> 00:21:47,958
You've got a secret power.

474
00:21:48,166 --> 00:21:49,875
[gasps] Yeah, it does!

475
00:21:50,250 --> 00:21:51,583
[chuckles]

476
00:21:51,791 --> 00:21:53,333
All right, back to bed.

477
00:21:54,583 --> 00:21:56,958
I've still got some
leftover work to finish up.

478
00:21:57,208 --> 00:21:58,208
Huh.

479
00:21:58,416 --> 00:21:59,208
Yay!

480
00:21:59,416 --> 00:22:00,458
Bed for me.

481
00:22:00,666 --> 00:22:02,333
[giggles]

482
00:22:02,541 --> 00:22:09,000
♪ ♪

483
00:22:09,208 --> 00:22:11,916
[theme music]

484
00:22:12,125 --> 00:22:19,250
♪ ♪

485
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:42,708
NEXT TIME:
A HOMETOWN AND FRIENDS
